3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget calculates TIA/USDT funding rates using a premium index based on the perpetual contract price versus the spot price, with an interest rate component typically set at 0.01% per 8-hour period. The funding rate is capped at ±0.75% per interval to prevent extreme payments during volatile market conditions. When the funding rate is positive, long positions pay shorts; when negative, shorts pay longs, with payments automatically settled from trading account balances."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TIA","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TIA represents Celestia's modular blockchain infrastructure, experiencing significant funding rate volatility due to its positioning in the emerging modular blockchain narrative. The token's mid-tier volume on Bitget creates opportunities for funding rate arbitrage, particularly during periods of heightened interest in data availability solutions and modular architecture developments."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TIA funding rates on Bitget have shown distinct patterns correlating with broader DeFi infrastructure sentiment and modular blockchain adoption cycles. During periods of high developer activity on Celestia's network, funding rates tend to skew positive as speculators take long positions anticipating ecosystem growth. The 8-hour settlement frequency allows for multiple arbitrage opportunities per day, with rates typically ranging from -0.1% to +0.3% per interval. Weekend periods often see reduced funding rate volatility as institutional trading activity decreases."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget's TIA/USDT perpetual offers arbitrage opportunities through cross-exchange funding rate differentials and spot-futures basis trading. The exchange's competitive fee structure makes it attractive for delta-neutral strategies where traders can capture funding payments while hedging directional exposure through spot TIA holdings. Copy trading features on Bitget can amplify funding rate imbalances as retail traders follow popular positions, creating temporary arbitrage windows. Integration with Bitget's spot market enables efficient basis trading execution."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TIA's infrastructure token status introduces unique risks including regulatory uncertainty around data availability layers and competition from other modular blockchain solutions. Bitget's relatively newer market presence compared to established exchanges may result in lower liquidity during stress periods, potentially affecting funding rate arbitrage execution. The exchange's 8-hour funding intervals create gap risk where significant price movements between settlements can erode arbitrage profits. Traders should monitor Celestia network developments and validator activity as these directly impact TIA token demand and funding rate dynamics."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are the funding rate settlement times for TIA/USDT on Bitget?","answer":"TIA/USDT funding rates settle every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. Bitget calculates the rate 15 minutes before settlement using the average premium over the previous 8-hour period."},{"question":"How does Bitget's fee structure affect TIA funding rate arbitrage profitability?","answer":"Bitget charges 0.02% maker fees and 0.06% taker fees on TIA/USDT perpetuals. For funding rate arbitrage, these fees must be factored against expected funding payments, typically requiring funding rates above 0.08% per interval to be profitable after round-trip costs."},{"question":"What is the maximum funding rate cap for TIA/USDT on Bitget?","answer":"Bitget caps TIA/USDT funding rates at ±0.75% per 8-hour interval to prevent excessive funding payments during extreme market conditions. This represents a maximum annualized funding rate of approximately ±820%."},{"question":"How does TIA's infrastructure token status affect funding rate patterns?","answer":"As Celestia's data availability token, TIA funding rates correlate with modular blockchain adoption trends and developer activity. Infrastructure tokens often experience persistent funding rate premiums during technology adoption phases as investors maintain long-term positions."}]}]
